{{Infobox Paralympic event |event = Mixed 50m Free Pistol SH1 |games = 2004 Summer |image = [[File:Shooting pictogram (Paralympics).svg|100px]] |caption = Paralympic Shooting |win_value = 621.7 | win_label = Winning points |venue = Markopoulo Olympic Shooting Centre |dates = 23 September 2004 |competitors = 27 |nations = 17 |gold = [[Andrey Lebedinsky]] |goldNPC = RUS |silver = [[Roland Hartmann]] |silverNPC = GER |bronze = [[Muharrem Korhan Yamac]] |bronzeNPC = TUR |prev = [[Shooting at the 2000 Summer Paralympics – Mixed 50 metre pistol SH1|2000]] |next = [[Shooting at the 2008 Summer Paralympics – Mixed 50 metre pistol SH1|2008]] }}{{ShootingAt2004SummerParalympics}}
The '''Mixed 50m Free Pistol SH1''' shooting event at the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]] was competed on 23 September.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athens2004.com/en/ParalympicResults/paralympics/results?rsc=SH0000000|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20041010180739/http://www.athens2004.com/en/ParalympicResults/paralympics/results?rsc=SH0000000|title=Schedule & Results - Shooting|archivedate=10 October 2004|accessdate=21 October 2012|publisher=Athens 2004 Paralympic Games }}</ref> It was won by [[Andrey Lebedinsky]], representing {{flagIPC|RUS|2004 Summer}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.paralympic.org/ipc_results/results.php?competition=2004PG&gender=x&sport=shooting&discipline=&event=Free%20Pistol&eclass=SH1|title=Mixed Free Pistol SH1|accessdate=21 October 2012|publisher=International Paralympic Committee}}</ref>
