{{Infobox_nrhp | name = Lincoln Statue | nrhp_type = | image = | caption = | location=Junction of Lincoln Way and Chestnut St., [[Jefferson, Iowa]] | lat_degrees = 42 | lat_minutes = 0 | lat_seconds = 56 | lat_direction = N | long_degrees = 94 | long_minutes = 21 | long_seconds = 58 | long_direction = W | locmapin = Iowa | area = | built = 1918 | architect= W. Granville Hastings | architecture= | added = March 29, 1993 | governing_body = Local | mpsub= | refnum= 93000165<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2009a}}</ref> }} '''Lincoln Statue''' is an historic structure located on the grounds of the [[Greene County Courthouse (Iowa)|Greene County Courthouse]] in [[Jefferson, Iowa]], [[United States]]. It was erected in 1918 and listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1993.<ref name="nris"/> The statue is a replica of W. Granville Hastings’ statue in [[Cincinnati, Ohio]],<ref name= Lincoln>{{cite web|url= http://showcase.netins.net/web/creative/lincoln/art/jefferson.htm |title= Hastings Statue in Jefferson, Iowa |publisher= AbrahamLincolnOnline.Org | accessdate=2011-03-15|last=|first=}}</ref> and was a gift of Mr. and Mrs. S. B. Wilson.
