{{Other uses|Mežciems (disambiguation){{!}}Mežciems}}
{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Mežciems''' is a neighbourhood of [[Riga]], [[Latvia]].  It is located in the eastern part of the city.  The name is literally translated from [[Latvian language|Latvian]] as 'forest village'.  Mežciems is encircled by Šmerlis and Jugla forests.  In the northern part of the neighbourhood there is Gaiļezers lake.  In its beginnings Mežciems was part of Dreiliņi county characterized by [[Single-family detached home|Single-family houses]].  The northern part of Mežciems was included in Riga in 1934.  The southern part of Mežciems was built in 1970s, when several [[apartment building]]s were constructed, and included in city in 1974.

