{{expand Portuguese|Universidade Estadual de Ponta Grossa|date=July 2012}} {{Infobox University |name = State University of Ponta Grossa(PT: Universidade Estadual de Ponta Grossa) |image = Uepg.jpg |motto = |established = 1969 |type = [[Public University]] |rector = Joao Carlos Gomes |city = [[Ponta Grossa]] |state = [[Paraná (state)|Parana]] |country = [[Brazil]] |undergrad = |postgrad = |students = 10,739 |faculty = 948 (Headcount) |campus = [[Urban area|Urban]] |free_label = |mascot = |free = |website= [http://www.uepg.br/ www.uepg.br] }}
The '''State University of Ponta Grossa''' ("Universidade Estadual de Ponta Grossa" in Portuguese) is one of the five state universities in [[Paraná (state)|Paraná]], [[Brazil]]. The institution has two campi in [[Ponta Grossa]] city as well as a college ground in each of the following cities: [[Telêmaco Borba]], [[Palmeira, Paraná|Palmeira]], [[Castro, Paraná|Castro]], [[São Mateus do Sul]] e [[Jaguariaíva]].
UEPG has 28 undergraduate courses as well as several post graduation courses leading to a PhD degree. The university has over 10.000 students and more than 1.500 faculty and staff members.
The university is also known in Brazil as a center of excellence in [[Journalism]], [[Tourism]], [[Law]], [[Biology]], [[Pedagogy]], [[Chemistry]], [[Dentistry]],<ref>[http://www.udc.edu.br/?action=viewpage&id=E2B5E2109326 UDC.edu.br<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and, according to the [[Webometrics Ranking of World Universities]], is on the Top100 universities of Latin America.<ref>[http://www.webometrics.info/top100_continent_es.asp?cont=latin_america <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
