{{Infobox UK constituency main |name = Stalybridge and Hyde |parliament = uk |map1 = StalybridgeHyde2007 |map2 = EnglandGreaterManchester |map_entity = Greater Manchester |map_year = |year = 1918 |abolished = |type = County |previous = [[Stalybridge (UK Parliament constituency)|Stalybridge]], [[Hyde (UK Parliament constituency)|Hyde]] and [[Mossley (UK Parliament constituency)|Mossley]] |next = |electorate = 70,691 (December 2010)<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.boundarycommissionforengland.org.uk/electoral-figures/electoral-figures.htm|title=Electorate Figures - Boundary Commission for England|date=4 March 2011|work=2011 Electorate Figures|publisher=Boundary Commission for England|accessdate=13 March 2011}}</ref> |mp = [[Jonny Reynolds]] |party = [[Labour Co-operative|Labour Co-op]] |region = England |county = [[Greater Manchester]] |european = North West England |elects_howmany = One |towns = [[Hyde, Greater Manchester|Hyde]], [[Mossley]], [[Stalybridge]] }}
'''Stalybridge and Hyde''' is a [[county constituency]] represented in the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]] of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]]. It elects one [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) by the [[first past the post]] system of election.
== Boundaries ==
The constituency covers the areas of the former [[municipal borough]]s of [[Stalybridge]], [[Hyde, Greater Manchester|Hyde]] and [[Mossley]], as well as the former [[Urban district (Great Britain and Ireland)|urban districts]] of [[Hollingworth]] and [[Mottram in Longdendale]]. Until 1997 it also included the area of the former municipal borough of Dukinfield, most of which now forms part of the [[Denton and Reddish (UK Parliament constituency)|Denton and Reddish]] constituency.
It is made up of the following Tameside Borough Council electoral wards, almost completely unchanged from the 1983 general election<ref>{{cite book|last=Crewe|first=Ivor|title=British Parliamentary Constituencies - a statistical compendium|year=1983|publisher=faber and faber|isbn=0-571-13236-7}}</ref>
* [[Dukinfield]] [[Stalybridge]], [[Hyde, Greater Manchester|Hyde]] Godley, Hyde Newton, Hyde Werneth, [[Longdendale]], Mossley, [[Stalybridge]] North, Stalybridge South.
===Proposed changes===
As part of the [[Sixth Periodic Review of Westminster constituencies]] which began in 2011 the Boundary Commission for England proposed expanding the seat<ref>[http://assets.boundarycommissionforengland.independent.gov.uk/proposals/141%20Greater%20Manchester/Stalybridge%20and%20Hyde%20CC.pdf Proposed map - Stalybridge and Hyde] Boundary Commission for England</ref> to incorporate Dukinfield as was the case in 1983.
== History ==
The constituency is a largely working-class area, and is a [[safe seat]] for [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]], which has held it since the [[United Kingdom general election, 1945|1945 general election]]. Its current [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) is [[Jonny Reynolds]], elected at the 2010 election to replace [[James Purnell]], a former [[10 Downing Street|Downing Street]] special advisor, who was first elected at the [[United Kingdom general election, 2001|2001 general election]]. He resigned his cabinet position as [[Work and Pensions Secretary]] on 4 June 2009, citing concerns over [[Prime Minister]] [[Gordon Brown]]'s leadership. On 19 February 2010, he announced that he would not contest the [[United Kingdom general election, 2010|2010 election]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/politics/article7033290.ece|title=James Purnell quits Parliament for a 'normal life'|work=The Times|date=20 February 2010|author=Webster, Philip|location=London}}</ref> There was concern among senior Labour Party officials that the [[Unite the Union|Unite]] union was attempting to get senior Unite official Peter Wheeler selected as Labour candidate in the constituency, leading to the [[National Executive Committee|NEC]] getting Jonny Reynolds on the selection shortlist.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/politics/2010/mar/16/secret-unite-plan-labour-safe-seats|title=No 10 acts over 'secret' Unite plan to fill safe seats|work= The Guardian|date=16 March 2010|author=Wintour, Patrick|location=London}}</ref>
== Members of Parliament == * ''Before 1918, see the two predecessor constiuencies: [[Hyde (UK Parliament constituency)|Hyde]] and also [[Stalybridge (UK Parliament constituency)|Stalybridge]]''
