'''Verkhivtseve''' ({{lang-uk|Верхівцеве}}, {{lang-ru|Верховцево}}) is a village in [[Dnipropetrovsk Oblast]] ([[oblast|province]]) of [[Ukraine]]. Population is 10,142 (2001). It has a railway station. The area is mostly forested. The modern name is appropriated on January, 1 1904 in honour first chief Ekaterininskoy railway, engineer Verkhivtseve. The settlement of Verkhivtseve got status of city in 1956.

