{{cleanup|date=June 2008}}

'''Poppers''' are an interesting [[fishing lure]] to add to any tackle box they come in a variety of sizes and colours.  The body is hollow, which keeps it on the waters surface. As you jerk your rod the lure pops along the surface using its concave head which in turn throws up bubbles and splashes which makes this lure very deadly for [[Bass (fish)|bass]] indeed.  The idea behind the lure is that to a predator fish this type of lure looks like a distressed fish.

