{{Infobox settlement |name=Lipník |settlement_type=Municipality |image_skyline=|image_shield=|image_flag=Lipník TR flag.svg |coordinates_region=CZ |subdivision_type=Country |subdivision_name={{CZE}} |subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]] |subdivision_name1=[[Vysočina Region|Vysočina]] |subdivision_type2=[[Districts of the Czech Republic|District]] |subdivision_name2=[[Třebíč District|Třebíč]] |latd=49|latm=8|lats=31|latNS=N|longd=15|longm=57|longs=3|longEW=E |pushpin_map=Czech Republic|coordinates_display=title |area_total_km2=5.14 |population_total=334|population_as_of=2006 |population_density_km2=auto |elevation_m=482 |postal_code_type=Postal&nbsp;code|postal_code=675&nbsp;52 |website=http://www.obeclipnik.cz }}
'''Lipník''' is a village and municipality (''[[obec]]'') in [[Třebíč District]] in the [[Vysočina Region]] of the Czech Republic.
The municipality covers an area of {{convert|5.14|km2|sqmi}}, and has a population of 334 (as at 3&nbsp;July 2006).
Lipník lies approximately {{convert|11|km|mi|0}} south-east of [[Třebíč]], {{convert|39|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Jihlava]], and {{convert|153|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Prague]].
