'''Arthur Addison Studenroth''' (October 9, 1899 - March 14, 1992) was an [[United States|American]] athlete who competed mainly in the Cross Country Team.

He competed for the United States in the [[1924 Summer Olympics]] held in [[Paris]], [[France]] in the Cross Country Team where he won the silver medal with his team mates [[Earl Johnson (athlete)|Earl Johnson]] and [[August Fager]].

