{{Infobox rail line | name = {{color box|#{{SCAX color|Ventura County}}}} Ventura County Line | image = Chatsworth Station2.jpg | image_width = 300px | caption = The Metrolink station at Chatsworth | type = [[regional rail|Commuter rail line]] | system = [[Metrolink (Southern California)|Metrolink]] | status = Operating | locale = [[Greater Los Angeles Area]] and [[Ventura County, California|Ventura County]] | start = [[Union Station (Los Angeles)|Los Angeles Union Station]] | end = [[East Ventura (Metrolink station)|East Ventura]] | stations = 12 | routes = | ridership = 3,950 (2012)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metrolinktrains.com/pdfs/Facts&Numbers/Fact_Sheets/Fact_Sheet_June_2012_Q4.pdf|title=Metrolink Fact Sheet for June 2012|work=Metrolink|accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref> | open = | close = | owner = | operator = [[Metrolink (Southern California)|Metrolink]] | character = Elevated and surface-level | stock = | linelength = {{convert|70.9|mi}} <small>(average length between stations: 6.445 miles)</small> | tracklength = | notrack = | gauge = {{RailGauge|sg}} | el = | speed = {{convert|39.22|mph|abbr=on}} (average for trains that travel the full line length on Mon-Fri) | elevation = | map = {{infobox rdt|Ventura County Line map|navbar=1}} }}
The [[Metrolink (Southern California)|Metrolink]] '''Ventura County Line''' is a [[commuter rail]] line serving [[Ventura County]] and the [[San Fernando Valley]] in [[Los Angeles County]] and the [[Los Angeles, California|City of Los Angeles]], in the [[Southern California]] system.<ref>{{cite news |title= Metrolink, The commuter railroad serving Los Angeles |url= http://www.trains.com/trn/default.aspx?c=a&id=401 |first= Matt Van|last= Hattem|date= June 30, 2006 |work= Trains Magazine| accessdate= 2006-10-10}}</ref>
==Schedules== Metrolink trains on the Ventura County Line run weekdays only, mostly during peak [[commuter]] hours, and so with limited midday service. From [[Union Station (Los Angeles)|Union Station]]—[[Downtown Los Angeles]] (as 7-2011): ;East Ventura *six trains total at peak hours, in the peak direction only (3 south-AM; 3 north PM) each weekday, running to [[East Ventura (Metrolink station)|East Ventura station]] (in the community of [[Montalvo, California|Montalvo]]) — northern end of line. ;Moorpark *four trains each weekday run to [[Moorpark (Amtrak station)|Moorpark Station]] (far western Simi Valley) — also station for Amtrak Pacific Surfliner. Trains of the six East Ventura runs also stop here. ;Chatsworth *three trains each weekday run to [[Chatsworth (Amtrak station)|Chatsworth Station]] (western SFValley) — major transit hub, with the Amtrak [[Pacific Surfliner]], the [[Orange Line (Los Angeles Metro)|Metro Orange Line]] (6-2012) and [[Metro Local (Los Angeles County)|Metro Local]] valley bus lines, the [[LADOT Commuter Express]] service; and buses from [[City of Santa Clarita Transit|Santa Clarita Transit]], and [[List of small Southern California transit agencies#Simi Valley Transit|Simi Valley Transit]]. Trains of the six East Ventura and four Moorpark runs also stop here. ;Airport *six trains each weekday run to Burbank-[[Bob Hope Airport]] (900 numbered series).
===Other service=== Service is augmented during midday and on weekends by the [[Amtrak]] [[Pacific Surfliner]] line, serving most of the Metrolink stations on the Ventura County Line.
;Airport Additional airport shuttle service operates between Union Station and Bob Hope Airport station as the '''Burbank-Bob Hope Airport Line'''—'''BUR'''. Metrolink numbers Airport Line trains in the 900 series.<ref>http://www.metrolinktrains.com/schedules/html.php?id=701</ref>
==Tracks== Metrolink owns the tracks between Moorpark and Los Angeles Union Station. It uses the [[Coast Line (UP)|Coast Line]] of the [[Union Pacific Railroad]] between Moorpark and [[Oxnard]] where the Santa Paula Branch splits from the rest of the Coast Line. The [[East Ventura (Metrolink station)|East Ventura Station]] and layover facility are on the Santa Paula branch line.
==History== {{seealso|CalTrain}} Service on this line began in 1992 as one of Metrolink's original three lines, with service from [[Moorpark]] to [[Los Angeles Union Station]] in [[Downtown Los Angeles]]. The line was extended to [[Camarillo]] and [[Oxnard]] in 1994 after the [[Northridge earthquake]], then to [[East Ventura (Metrolink station)|East Ventura]] in 2002.
===Accidents=== {{main|2008 Chatsworth train collision}} At 4:23 p.m. on September 12, 2008, 25 people were killed in a collision between Metrolink commuter train 111 and a freight train. At least 130 people were injured, with at least one dying later at a hospital. The crash occurred on the Ventura County Line near Heather Lee Lane, south of the Ronald Reagan (118) Freeway and east of Topanga Canyon Boulevard. Both locomotives, the leading car of the commuter train, and seven cars of the freight train were derailed.
